JOHANNESBURG – The South African Communist Party (SACP) has reacted to President Jacob Zuma’s decision to fire Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande. “This is a clear declaration of war on the SACP by President Zuma,” the SACP's Solly Mapaila said. “He has retained dead wood in that Cabinet,” he added. SACP's Solly Mapaila on #CabinetReshuffle - "This is a clear declaration of war on the SACP by President Zuma." Courtesy DStv 403 pic.twitter.com/cdkXnC1iMP Mapaila accused Zuma of being detached from the ANC. SACP's Mapaila on President Zuma and the #CabinetReshuffle. Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/pRbM1xedNT eNCA